of, Titanic, in 1985.

00:26:44.590 --> 00:26:50.200
I actually asked him, I
asked the silliest question.

00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:52.290
What makes you more
nervous, actually public

00:26:52.290 --> 00:26:56.320
speaking or exploring
the undersea world?

00:26:56.320 --> 00:26:59.300
He said, Carmine, almost
dying 2 and 1/2 miles

00:26:59.300 --> 00:27:02.500
beneath the surface of the
Atlantic is a lot scarier

00:27:02.500 --> 00:27:03.880
any public speaking.

00:27:03.880 --> 00:27:07.130
He has no stage fright anymore.

00:27:07.130 --> 00:27:10.320
He said, your mission
in any presentation

00:27:10.320 --> 00:27:15.412
is to inform,
educate, and inspire.

00:27:15.412 --> 00:27:16.120
Think about that.

00:27:16.120 --> 00:27:17.340
That's a powerful line.

00:27:17.340 --> 00:27:19.740
You can only inspire
when you give people

00:27:19.740 --> 00:27:24.240
a new way of looking at the
world in which they live.

00:27:24.240 --> 00:27:28.650
Researchers call that new way
an emotionally charged event.

00:27:28.650 --> 00:27:32.690
It simply means that when
you perceive something

00:27:32.690 --> 00:27:37.770
that is fresh, unexpected,
surprising, and new,

00:27:37.770 --> 00:27:39.850
it actually creates
that dopamine

00:27:39.850 --> 00:27:41.630
hit that I told you about.

00:27:41.630 --> 00:27:43.720
It's called, in the
academic research,

00:27:43.720 --> 00:27:45.620
an emotionally charged event.

