temperature increases,

00:41:01.900 --> 00:41:04.800
which leads to some
really bad things.

00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:09.330
OK, he's trying to
simplify complexities.

00:41:09.330 --> 00:41:12.710
When you simplify complexities,
you need a simple slide.

00:41:12.710 --> 00:41:16.180
So that's an actual slide from
a Bill Gates presentation.

00:41:16.180 --> 00:41:18.190
You can do this--
I remember working

00:41:18.190 --> 00:41:21.200
for LinkedIn before
they went IPO.

00:41:21.200 --> 00:41:24.450
They started using some
picture superiority

00:41:24.450 --> 00:41:27.750
to explain what they did,
especially in the marketing

00:41:27.750 --> 00:41:28.250
department.

00:41:28.250 --> 00:41:30.110
This is a before slide.

00:41:30.110 --> 00:41:31.890
This is an after slide.

00:41:31.890 --> 00:41:33.440
So you see the difference.

00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:35.160
Here, it's a lot of numbers.

00:41:35.160 --> 00:41:37.880
The most important
numbers get lost.

00:41:37.880 --> 00:41:39.460
But if that's all
I want you to know

00:41:39.460 --> 00:41:42.200
is how many members we have
and how many members we're

00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:45.260
