can tell this is an old slide.

00:41:45.260 --> 00:41:47.450
Only 70 million.

00:41:47.450 --> 00:41:49.420
This was before
they event went IPO.

00:41:49.420 --> 00:41:51.990
But again, it's let's
think about how are we

00:41:51.990 --> 00:41:56.010
going to display
information visually.

00:41:56.010 --> 00:41:59.930
Those are the three
components that all inspiring

00:41:59.930 --> 00:42:02.070
presentations need to have.

00:42:02.070 --> 00:42:04.710
They all need to be emotional.

00:42:04.710 --> 00:42:06.940
Passion, storytelling.

00:42:06.940 --> 00:42:08.330
They all need to be novel.

00:42:08.330 --> 00:42:11.790
Teach me something new,
unexpected, fresh, surprising.

00:42:11.790 --> 00:42:13.122
And of course, memorable.

00:42:13.122 --> 00:42:14.830
There are a number of
techniques that you

00:42:14.830 --> 00:42:17.610
can use to make sure
that people recall

00:42:17.610 --> 00:42:19.640
the information that
you've given them.

00:42:19.640 --> 00:42:22.710
Above all, keep this in
mind-- that you do all

00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:25.900
have the capacity
to move people.

00:42:25.900 --> 00:42:29.790
You all have the capacity
to educate, to electrify,

00:42:29.790 --> 00:42:31.680
to inform, to inspire.

00:42:31.680 --> 00:42:33.470
You have ideas.

00:42:33.470 --> 00:42:37.460
All of you have big,
bold, transcendent ideas

00:42:37.460 --> 00:42:39.710
that need to be heard.

00:42:39.710 --> 00:42:43.970
Please communicate those ideas
as persuasively as possible

00:42:43.970 --> 00:42:45.870
because we need to
hear those ideas

00:42:45.870 --> 00:42:49.025
and we need to be able
to act on your ideas.

00:42:49.025 --> 00:42:51.150
Thank you very much for
inviting me this afternoon.

